{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban the use of blanket 'no children' clauses in rental contracts",
        "additional_details": "The council housing aren\u2019t able to offer assistance to many families for a while, if at all, if they\u2019re living with a family member or friend for example. Every parent wants a roof over their children\u2019s head and stability, not living in \u2018temporary\u2019 accommodation with a family/friend for months/years & in some cases in a single bedroom!",
        "background": "Prevent landlords from discriminating and create a legal framework to stop blanket 'no children' clauses.\r\n \r\nSome landlords are refusing to let their property because the person(s) have children. I believe this is discrimination & shouldn\u2019t be allowed.",
